    "causal_summary": "The graph-metadata generator re-derives the causal_summary and the description but persists no proof they were re-derived from the current source docs, the phase-child contract is split across isPhaseParent and resolveChildrenIds which can disagree, and access and freshness telemetry stored in the generated JSON mutate the file on reads and resumes so a no-op read dirties an unchanged file. This phase persists a source_fingerprint derived over the volatile-ignoring projection, unifies the child contract behind one shared listPhaseChildren helper, and moves last_accessed_at and the phase-parent pointers into the DB or index layer, all behind a default-off flag and a grandfather report mode so existing files that carry prose statuses and prefixed paths the new contract rejects do not mass-fail. The research ranks both recommendations P2 because graph metadata is already idempotent, so the fingerprint is hardening and the telemetry split is a larger refactor scoped after the P0 and P1 work.",
